label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pT1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma involving the conjunctiva alone without eyelid or orbital involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pT2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma with orbital involvement with or without conjunctival involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pT3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma with preseptal eyelid involvement with or without orbital involvement and with or without conjunctival involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pT4 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Orbital adnexal lymphoma and extraorbital lymphoma extending beyond the orbit to adjacent structures, such as bone, maxillofacial sinuses, and brain. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Membrane Localization Motif

value.value: An amino acid sequence that directs a protein to become localized in or at the cell membrane. This targeting is determined either by the presence of hydrophobic amino acid residues or by post-translational modification that adds a hydrophobic molecule to the protein at this site.

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ocular adnexal lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Involvement of lymph nodes not assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma with no evidence of lymph node involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma with involvement of lymph node region or regions draining the ocular adnexal structures and superior to the mediastinum (preauricular, parotid, submandibular, and cervical nodes). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma with involvement of a single lymph node region superior to the mediastinum. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma with involvement of two or more lymph node regions, superior to the mediastinum. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma with involvement of lymph node regions of the mediastinum. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma with diffuse or disseminated involvement of peripheral and central lymph node regions. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Office Staff was Friendly and Kind

value.value: A question about whether an individual's office staff was friendly and kind.

label.value: Office Staff Made You Feel Comfortable

value.value: A question about whether an individual's office staff made them feel comfortable.

label.value: Monobasic Proteolytic Cleavage Site

value.value: A site on a protein that is a target for enzymatic cleavage, where the residue on the amino terminal side of the cleavage site is a basic amino acid that is not adjacent to other basic amino acids.

label.value: Office Staff was Thorough

value.value: A question about whether an individual's office staff was thorough.

label.value: Office Staff Made Time for Your Concerns

value.value: A question about whether an individual's office staff made time for their concerns.

label.value: Graded Prognostic Assessment

value.value: A prognostic index for patients with brain metastases. The GPA incorporates age, Karnofsky performance status, number of extracranial metastases, and number of brain metastases.

label.value: Disease-specific Graded Prognostic Assessment

value.value: A 4-tiered score that stratifies patients with common primary tumours metastasizing to the brain (malignant melanoma, lung, breast, kidney and gastrointestinal cancers) into subgroups with different prognoses. It takes into account that brain metastases from different primary tumor sites respond differently to radiation therapy.

label.value: Graded Prognostic Assessment Score

value.value: A 4-tiered score that stratifies patients with common primary tumors metastasizing to the brain (malignant melanoma, lung, breast, kidney and gastrointestinal cancers) into subgroups with different prognoses. The score is based on age, Karnofsky performance status, number of extracranial metastases, number of brain metastases, and site of primary tumor.

label.value: Robot-Assisted Surgery

value.value: A surgical technique that uses a specially designed robotic system to aid with the surgical procedure.

label.value: Ivor Lewis Esophagectomy

value.value: A type of esophagectomy where an esophageal tumor is removed through an abdominal incision and a right thoracotomy. The esophagogastric anastomosis is located in the upper chest.

label.value: McKeown Esophagectomy

value.value: A type of esophagectomy that involves a right thoracotomy, laparotomy, and left neck incision for creation of a cervical anastomosis. It is appropriate in patients with tumors located above the gastro-esophageal junction up to the level of the clavicles and is the preferred approach for locally advanced esophageal carcinomas.

label.value: Transhiatal Esophagectomy

value.value: A type of esophagectomy where the esophageal tumor is removed through an abdominal incision and a left neck incision, without a thoracotomy. The esophagogastric anastomosis is located in the neck.

label.value: Mandard Grading System

value.value: A tumor regression grading (TRG) system commonly used for upper gastrointestinal carcinomas.

label.value: Nuclear Localization Signal

value.value: An amino acid sequence that directs the post-translational transport of a protein to the nucleus. The sequence contains positively charged amino acids such as arginine and lysine.

label.value: Tumor Regression Grade 1

value.value: Complete regression; fibrosis without detectable tumor.

label.value: Tumor Regression Grade 2

value.value: Presence of fibrosis with scattered tumor cells.

label.value: Tumor Regression Grade 3

value.value: Presence of fibrosis and tumor cells with a preponderance of fibrosis.

label.value: Tumor Regression Grade 4

value.value: Presence of fibrosis and tumor cells with preponderance of tumor cells.

label.value: Tumor Regression Grade 5

value.value: Presence of tumor without changes of regression.

label.value: Endocrine System Cancer TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of endocrine system cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Thyroid Carcinoma TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of thyroid carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of papillary, follicular, Hurthle cell, poorly differentiated, and anaplastic (undifferentiated) thyroid carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. Medullary thyroid cancers are staged according to the classification for thyroid-medullary. Thyroid lymphomas are staged according to the classification for Hodgkin and non-Hodgkin lymphoma. There are no AJCC staging systems for thyroid cancer arising from thyroglossal duct cyst and thyroid cancer in malignant struma ovarii. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma Clinical TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of papillary, follicular, Hurthle cell, poorly differentiated, and anaplastic thyroid carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of papillary, follicular, Hurthle cell, poorly differentiated, and anaplastic thyroid carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Carbenicillin Indanyl Sodium

value.value: The sodium salt of indanyl carbenicillin, a broad-spectrum, semi-synthetic carboxypenicillin antibiotic with bactericidal activity. Carbenicillin acylates C-terminal domain of penicillin-sensitive transpeptidase, resulting in opening the lactam ring of the antibiotic. This inactivation prevents the formation of the cross-linkage of peptidoglycan strands, thereby inhibiting the third and last stage of bacterial cell wall synthesis. As a result, cell wall integrity is compromised and cell lysis may follow. This agent is used mainly for gram-negative infections, and has limited gram-positive coverage.

label.value: Signal Peptide

value.value: The N-terminal sequence of a secreted protein that interacts with a signal recognition particle and is required for transport through the cell membrane.

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma cM0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma cM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma Clinical Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of papillary, follicular, Hurthle cell, poorly differentiated, and anaplastic thyroid carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma cNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma cN0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: No evidence of locoregional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma cN0b TNM Finding v8

value.value: No radiologic or clinical evidence of locoregional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma cN1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Metastasis to regional nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma cN1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Metastasis to level VI or VII (pretracheal, paratracheal, or prelaryngeal /Delphian, or upper mediastinal) lymph nodes. This can be unilateral or bilateral disease. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma cN1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Metastasis to unilateral, bilateral, or contralateral lateral neck lymph nodes (levels I, II, III, IV, or V) or retropharyngeal lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Papillary, Follicular, Hurthle Cell, Poorly Differentiated, and Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma Pathologic TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of papillary, follicular, Hurthle cell, poorly differentiated, and anaplastic thyroid carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: RNA Binding Domain

value.value: RNA Binding Domains, such as the RRM, RGG box, and KH domain, mediate the interaction of RNAs with RNA-binding proteins. RRMs of about 90 amino acids consist of a four-stranded beta sheet adjacent to two alpha helixes. Within RRMs, conserved RNP-1 and RNP-2 motifs on the central beta sheets lie side by side; their side chains contact RNA. Found in hnRNP proteins, the RGG box is an RNA-binding motif containing five Arg-Gly-Gly repeats with intervening aromatic residues. The KH domain is found in several RNA-binding proteins in multiple repeats interspersed with RGG boxes. (NCI)
